.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINTIME.WITH" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainTime.with \- Temporal.PlainTime.prototype.with()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]with()\f[B]\f[R] method of \f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R]
instances returns a new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R] object
representing this time with some fields replaced by new values.
Because all \f[CR]Temporal\f[R] objects are designed to be immutable,
this method essentially functions as the setter for the time\(cqs
fields.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
with(info)
with(info, options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]info\f[R]
An object containing at least one of the properties recognized by
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime.from()\f[R]: \f[CR]hour\f[R],
\f[CR]microsecond\f[R], \f[CR]millisecond\f[R], \f[CR]minute\f[R],
\f[CR]nanosecond\f[R], \f[CR]second\f[R].
Unspecified properties use the values from the original time.
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An object containing the following property:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]overflow\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A string specifying the behavior when a time component is out of range.
Possible values are:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]\(dqconstrain\(dq\f[R] (default)
The time component is clamped to the valid range.
.TP
\f[B]\(dqreject\(dq\f[R]
A \f[CR]RangeError\f[R] is thrown if the time component is out of range.
.RE
.RE
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R] object, where the fields specified
in \f[CR]info\f[R] that are not \f[CR]undefined\f[R] are replaced by the
corresponding values, and the rest of the fields are copied from the
original time.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown in one of the following cases:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]info\f[R] is not an object with at least one recognized property
or a string.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]options\f[R] is not an object or \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
.RE
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown if the provided numerical properties are out of range, and
\f[CR]options.overflow\f[R] is set to \f[CR]\(dqreject\(dq\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using with()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] time = Temporal.PlainTime.from(\(dq12:34:56.123456789\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] newTime = time.with({ hour: 23 });
console.log(newTime.toString()); \f[I]// \(aq23:34:56.123456789\(aq\f[R]
.EE
.PP
For more examples, see the documentation for the individual properties
that can be set using \f[CR]with()\f[R].
